#: ../../T/tron.rst:5
msgid "tron"
msgstr "tron"

#: ../../T/tron.rst:7
msgid "v\\."
msgstr "動詞"

#: ../../T/tron.rst:9
msgid ""
"[NRL, CMU; prob. fr. the movie *Tron*\\] To become inaccessible except via "
"email or :manpage:`talk(1)`\\, especially when one is normally available via"
" telephone or in person. Frequently used in the past tense, as in: \"Ran "
"seems to have tronned on us this week\" or \"Gee, Ran, glad you were able to"
" un-tron yourself\". One may also speak of tron mode; compare :ref:`spod`\\."
msgstr ""
"[NRL、CMU。おそらく映画\\ *Tron*\\ より]通常は電話や対面で連絡が取れるのに、メールや\\ :manpage:`talk(1)`\\ "
"経由でしか連絡が取れなくなること。よく過去形で使われる:「Ranは今週、我々の前からtronしてしまったようだ」や「やあRan、un-"
"tronできてよかった」のように。tron modeと言うこともできる。\\ :ref:`spod`\\ と比較せよ。"

#: ../../T/tron.rst:15
msgid ""
"Note that many dialects of BASIC have a TRON/TROFF command pair that "
"enables/disables line number tracing; this has no obvious relationship to "
"the slang usage."
msgstr ""
"多くのBASICの方言には、行番号トレースを有効/無効にするTRON/TROFFというコマンドの対があることに注意。これはスラングの用法と明白な関係はない。"
